review_blob: Great looking dark beer with tan head.  Sweet smoked smell.  Good balanced flavor with little bitterness bite at end.  Not near as heavy as it looks.

Bomber--roasted smell with citrus dominance. Light hints of fruit with small alcohol burn.--nice copper color with off white head--nice initial taste with bitter burn at end--coats the mouth--overal too much citrus and harshness without a good enough flavor base for my tastes
beer_name: Fort Collins The Incredible Hop - Imperial Rye IPA
